# Auto-Create Project Rules

When the user asks for something that should persist across future sessions, add or update a rule in `.cursor/rules/` in the **same task** — do not wait to be asked again.

## Create a rule when the user asks for

- Coding standards, conventions, or patterns ("always use…", "never…", "prefer…")
- Project-wide workflows (env vars, layout, auth, CMS, database, testing)
- File/folder structure mandates (atomic design, naming, colocation)
- Tooling or stack-specific guidance (Prismic, Clerk, Neon, Tailwind, Yarn)
- Explicit requests: "add a rule", "remember this", "create a cursor rule"

## Do not create a rule for

- One-off implementation tasks with no ongoing convention
- Bug fixes or single-feature work unless the user also wants it codified
- Duplicating an existing rule — update the existing `.mdc` file instead

## Before writing

1. List existing rules in `.cursor/rules/` and avoid overlap
2. Prefer **one concern per rule**; split if the request spans unrelated topics
3. Choose scope:
   - `alwaysApply: true` — project-wide workflow (env files, server actions, rule creation)
   - `globs: ...` + `alwaysApply: false` — file-type or area-specific (components, CSS)

## Rule file requirements

- Path: `.cursor/rules/<kebab-case-name>.mdc`
- YAML frontmatter: `description`, and either `alwaysApply: true` or `globs`
- Body: concise, actionable, under ~50 lines when possible
- Include brief ✅/❌ examples when it clarifies behavior

## After creating or updating a rule

- Mention the new/updated rule path in the task summary
- If the rule introduces new env vars or setup steps, also update `.env.example` per `env-example.mdc`
- If the rule changes how developers run the project, add a short note to `README.md` only when relevant

## Examples

| User request | Action |
|--------------|--------|
| "Use grid unless flex is required" | Create `grid-first-layout.mdc` with `globs: src/**/*.{js,css}` |
| "Update .env.example when adding env vars" | Create `env-example.mdc` with `alwaysApply: true` |
| "Use server actions for mutations" | Already covered — update `server-actions.mdc` instead of duplicating |
| "Use Zod for forms" | Already covered — update `zod-forms.mdc` instead of duplicating |
| "Use Radix for UI primitives" | Already covered — update `radix-ui.mdc` instead of duplicating |
| "Which packages to use" | Already covered — update `package-usage.mdc` instead of duplicating |
